          "Darkness = Danger"
        ],
        "conceptSummary": [
          "The setting creates a mood of fear and isolation."
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "The Encounter: Mirror and Snake",
        "explanation": "While combing his hair, the doctor sees a cobra behind him in the mirror. The snake is calm, but he is terrified.",
        "keyPoints": [
          "The mirror acts as a tool for discovery.",
          "The snake's stillness contrasts with the doctor's panic."
        ],
        "examples": [
          "The doctor freezes when he sees the reflection."
        ],
        "whyItMatters": "This scene is the climax of the story, showing how fear can paralyze us.",
