          "Real-life situations where we avoid looking at problems."
        ],
        "visualSupport": [
          "A close-up of a mirror showing a snake's head behind a person."
        ],
        "importantNotes": [
          "The snake does not strike immediately; it waits."
        ],
        "memoryTechniques": [
          "Mirror = Truth Revealer"
        ],
        "conceptSummary": [
          "The mirror scene is the turning point of the story."
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "Character Analysis: The Doctor",
        "explanation": "The doctor is portrayed as a young, somewhat arrogant man who underestimates danger until it is too late.",
        "keyPoints": [
          "He is confident but not brave.",
          "His fear reveals his humanity."
        ],
        "examples": [
          "He tries to act cool before the snake strikes."
        ],
        "whyItMatters": "Understanding the doctor helps us analyze human behavior under stress.",
        "terminology": [
          "Character Arc",
          "Psychological State"
